  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).",
    "Slice onions thinly and coat with all-purpose flour.",
    "Heat coconut oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion slices and cook until translucent, about 15 minutes.",
    "Stir in red pepper flakes, cayenne pepper, salt, and paprika. Cook for an additional minute to meld flavors.",
    "Transfer to a greased baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 20 minutes or until crispy.",
    "Serve immediately."
